stone-menv

Installation

1. Build links

# assuming stone build directory is at $HOME/stone/build
$ cd stone-menv
$ ./build_links.sh

A different stone repository can be passed as the first argument to build_links.sh.

2. Configure shell environment

To your shell startup script (such as $HOME/.bashrc) add the following:

source ~/stone-menv/.menvrc

(modify line appropriately if stone-menv was installed at a different location)
